text: attending Spelman College was a dream
come true for this first generation
Brooklyn girl I gained knowledge of my
ancestors an undying Sisterhood from
women from all walks of life and
dedicated advocacy from committed
professors who encouraged me and my
journey toward becoming the advocate
college counselor and Coach that I am
today I have since been blessed to be
named one of New York City's Frontline
Heroes and recognized in Bloomberg's
black news and New York news media
highlighting the work I've done to
uplift and Inspire young people here in
New York but I do what I do not to
receive Awards or see my name appearing
in articles I do what I do because
helping the Next Generation realize
their dream is my dream my passion and
my caller
but the more initiative my hope is
finally focused on creating my own
non-profit around College access for
underprivileged students because my
dream is to see that young people's
dreams can continue on and on and on
just like mine was realized at Spelman
College
